whichever gate you desire","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 10, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRejoice! Rejoice! Verily, whoever performs the five prayers and avoids the major sins will enter Paradise from whichever gate he wishes.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 13\/8 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064d\u0648\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42172,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/08\/23\/if-avoid-kabair\/","url_meta":{"origin":41400,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Faith: Paradise if believers avoid major sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 23, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Ayyub reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever comes worshiping Allah without associating anything with Him, performing the prayer, giving the charity, and avoiding the major sins, he will have Paradise.\u201d They asked him about the major sins, and the Prophet said, \u201cIdolatry\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":20436,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/03\/05\/intercession-major-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":41400,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sins: We have hope for people of major sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 5, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: We withheld ourselves from seeking forgiveness for people of major sins until we heard our Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, say, \u201cVerily, I have delayed my intercession for the people of major sins among my nation for the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \"Thus,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42699,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/07\/despair-major-sin\/","url_meta":{"origin":41400,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Kaba\u2019ir: Despairing of Allah\u2019s mercy a major sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 7, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what are the major sins?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him said, \u201cIdolatry with Allah, losing hope in relief from Allah, and despair in the mercy of Allah.\u201d Source: Kashf al-Asta\u0304r 106 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28710,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/06\/major-sin-insult-twice\/","url_meta":{"origin":41400,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Insults: Major sin to over-retaliate to provocation","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, among the worst of major sins, is to attack the reputation of a Muslim man without a just cause, and among the major sins is to revile twice in response to one insult.\u201d Source: Sunan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37988,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/07\/19\/bidah-warning\/","url_meta":{"origin":41400,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Bid\u2019ah: Warning against glorifying innovators in religion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 19, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibrahim ibn Maysarah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever honors a heretical innovator has aided in the destruction of Islam.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 9018 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646 \u0625\u0650\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u064a\u0633\u0631\u064e\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\